# Localization

## 1. Applies when
Games shipping in multiple languages or targeting international markets.

## 2. This document owns
Localization strategy and language coverage; text extraction, string tables, and localization pipeline; font and typography support for target scripts (CJK, Arabic, Cyrillic, etc.); cultural adaptation guidelines (imagery, symbols, references); voice-over localization and dubbing specifications; locale-specific UI layout adjustments (text expansion, RTL); localization QA process and linguistic testing.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Original dialogue and narrative text (→ Narrative_Script); UI layout and interaction design (→ UI_UX_Design); font rendering and engine-level text support (→ Technical_Design); accessibility features (→ Accessibility).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Localization Strategy & Language Coverage · 2. Text Pipeline & String Tables · 3. Font & Typography Support · 4. Cultural Adaptation · 5. Voice-Over Localization · 6. Locale-Specific UI · 7. Localization QA & Linguistic Testing

## 5. Common boundaries
- Localization owns "how it's translated"; Narrative_Script owns "what is said".
- RTL / script-specific UI adaptations belong here; general UI design belongs to UI_UX_Design.
- Font support specs live here; font rendering implementation lives in Technical_Design.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Check that localized text references the original source in Narrative_Script.
- Check that locale count matches the declared language coverage.
